sentences: Harriet Mary Browne Owen (1798â€“1858) was an English writer and composer, the sister of poet Felicia Hemans.
Browne was a granddaughter of the Venetian consul in Liverpool, and the family moved from there to Denbighshire in North Wales for her father to pursue his business.
She grew up near Abergele and St. Asaph in Flintshire, and married a man named Owen.
